   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">Activating a program triggers jobs to create payout schedules. Primarily these payout schedules are created based on the settings of three attributes on the Program Definition.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The attributes include:</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">
         <table class="- topic/table ">
            <tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup ">
               <colspec colname="col1" class="- topic/colspec "/>
               <colspec colname="col2" class="- topic/colspec "/>
               <thead class="- topic/thead ">
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Fields</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Description</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </thead>
               <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Billing Frequency</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">The setting defines, the schedule frequency <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Monthly, Quarterly, Semi-Annual,</b> and <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Yearly.</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Program Schedule Day</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">The setting defines the dates to be considered for a period generation.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Ready For Invoice Day</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">The setting defines, the maximum number of days to accept the order lines for a previous period, before changing the status of the period to calculation complete.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </tbody>
            </tgroup>
         </table>
      </p>
